As of 2020, the total population of the entire Battery Park City area was recorded at 16,169 individuals, a figure that continues to evolve as the community matures and adapts. [60] [86] [87]

### Buildings

#### Residential

The inaugural residential building within Battery Park City, the imposing Gateway Plaza, reached completion in 1983, marking a significant milestone in the neighborhood's development. [60] [4] As of 2010, the population of the area had grown to 13,386 residents, inhabiting a diverse array of structures. Some of the more prominent residential buildings that define the Battery Park City skyline include:

[Southern part of Battery Park City; Millennium Point is shown.](/Millennium_Point)

*   **[Millennium Point](/Millennium_Point)**: This commanding 449-foot (137 m), 38-story [skyscraper](/Skyscraper) was meticulously constructed between 1999 and 2001. [88] It spans the street addresses 25–39 Battery Place, anchoring a significant corner of the neighborhood. [89] However, due to the horrific [September 11 attacks](/September_11_attacks) that struck the nearby [World Trade Center](/World_Trade_Center_(1973-2001)), the eagerly anticipated opening of Millennium Point was regrettably delayed until January 2002, a stark reminder of the tragedy's pervasive impact. [89] The building, a testament to modern design, was recognized with the prestigious 2001 Silver [Emporis Skyscraper Award](/Emporis_Skyscraper_Award). [88] The upper tower section of the building contains 113 luxurious condominiums, catering to an affluent clientele. [89] The wider, lower 12 floors are elegantly occupied by a 5-star hotel, The Wagner at the Battery (formerly known as the [Ritz-Carlton](/Ritz-Carlton) Battery Park). This opulent hotel boasts 298 rooms, including 44 lavish suites, with the largest suite offering a sprawling 200 square meters (2,150 sq ft) of living space. [89] The [Skyscraper Museum](/Skyscraper_Museum) occupies a concise, yet informative, space on the first floor of the building, offering insights into urban architecture. A sophisticated restaurant is conveniently situated on the 14th floor, providing elevated dining experiences with panoramic views.

*   **[The Solaire](/The_Solaire)**: Distinguished as the very first [green](/Green_building) residential building in the [United States](/United_States), [The Solaire](/The_Solaire) also holds the notable distinction of being the first residential high-rise in [New York City](/New_York_City) to achieve certification by the esteemed U.S. Green Building Council. [60] [90] Designed by the renowned architectural firm [Pelli Clarke Pelli](/Pelli_Clarke_Pelli), its construction was completed in 2003, ushering in a new era of sustainable urban living. [91] [The Solaire](/The_Solaire) is strategically located at 20 River Terrace, offering prime waterfront access. The developer of this groundbreaking project received crucial funding from the [State of New York](/New_York_(state)), a decision that was not without a degree of controversy. The developer was only required to commit to setting aside 10% of the units as "affordable housing" or "moderate income," a ratio that deviated from the more commonly mandated 80:20 agreement, raising questions about equity. Upon its grand opening, rents within [The Solaire](/The_Solaire) ranged from approximately $2,500 to $9,001, depending on the size and configuration of the unit, firmly establishing its luxury market position. The building has since achieved the prestigious [LEED](/Leadership_in_Energy_and_Environmental_Design) Platinum rating, a testament to its exceptional environmental performance. [92] Its energy-conserving design is remarkably 35% more energy-efficient than existing building codes require, resulting in a substantial 67% lower electricity demand during peak hours. This translates, among other significant benefits, to noticeably lower electric bills for its residents, a practical advantage of sustainable living. Photovoltaic panels are ingeniously integrated to convert sunlight directly into electricity, a clean and renewable energy source. This system is further augmented by a sophisticated computerized building management system and a commitment to environmentally responsible operating and maintenance practices, all meticulously implemented to further minimize the building's overall environmental footprint, making [The Solaire](/The_Solaire) a true pioneer in green urban development.

